<subSubSection id="C30175E2FFB0FFA3C6F4574CFB35F939" box="[199,1208,1663,1689]" pageId="4" pageNumber="205" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BA42669FFB0FFA3C6F4574CFB35F939" blockId="4.[151,1437,762,1905]" box="[199,1208,1663,1689]" pageId="4" pageNumber="205">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFB0FFA3C6F4574CFEC5F939" bold="true" box="[199,328,1663,1689]" pageId="4" pageNumber="205">Etymology</emphasis>
. The species epithet refers to the characters of pin-shaped setae on sternite VI.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
