<subSubSection id="C30175E2FFB0FFA3C6F4563CFB28F8D1" pageId="4" pageNumber="205" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA42669FFB0FFA3C6F4563CFB28F8D1" blockId="4.[151,1437,762,1905]" pageId="4" pageNumber="205">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFB0FFA3C6F4563CFEB9F889" bold="true" box="[199,308,1807,1833]" pageId="4" pageNumber="205">Remarks</emphasis>
. The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B5DEAFFB0FFA3C4BF563CFC74F889" authority="Liu et Cai, 2013" authorityName="Liu et Cai" authorityYear="2013" box="[652,1017,1807,1833]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Pseudacteon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="205" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadrisetalis">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFB0FFA3C4BF563CFCB4F889" box="[652,825,1807,1833]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="205">P. quadrisetalis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF8A5B98FFB0FFA3C573563CFC74F889" author="Liu, G. C. &amp; Wang, J. F. &amp; Cai, Y. L." box="[832,1017,1807,1833]" pageId="4" pageNumber="205" pagination="53 - 58" refId="ref22208" refString="Liu, G. C., Wang, J. F. &amp; Cai, Y. L. (2013) The ant-parasitizing genus Pseudacteon Coquillett (Diptera: Phoridae) from China with description of three new species. Entomologica Fennica, 24, 53 - 58. https: // doi. org / 10.33338 / ef. 7867" type="journal article" year="2013">
Liu 
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFB0FFA3C55D563CFC0FF888" box="[878,898,1807,1832]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="205">et</emphasis>
Cai, 2013
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, it differs from the latter by the upper supra-antennal setae shorter and thinner than other frontal setae, fore tarsomere 5 shorter than tarsomere 1, second section of wing vein costa shorter and the pin-shaped setae on sternite VI longer and thinner.
</paragraph>
